248 /// A file system according to your operating system. ----
249 /// This may be linked to the process's working directory, or maintain its own. ----
250 /// ----
251 /// Currently, its own working directory is emulated by storing the path and ----
252 /// sending absolute paths to llvm::sys::fs:: functions. ----
253 /// A more principled approach would be to push this down a level, modelling ----
254 /// the working dir as an llvm::sys::fs::WorkingDir or similar. ----
255 /// This would enable the use of openat()-style functions on some platforms. ----
256 class RealFileSystem : public FileSystem { ----
257 public: ----
258 explicit RealFileSystem(bool LinkCWDToProcess) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
259 if (!LinkCWDToProcess) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
260 SmallString<128> PWD, RealPWD; 0
261 if (std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::current_path(PWD)) 0
262 WD = EC; 0
263 else if (llvm::sys::fs::real_path(PWD, RealPWD)) 0
264 WD = WorkingDirectory{PWD, PWD}; 0
265 else ----
266 WD = WorkingDirectory{PWD, RealPWD}; 0
267 } 0
268 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
269 ----
270 ErrorOr status(const Twine &Path) override; ----
271 ErrorOr> openFileForRead(const Twine &Path) override; ----
272 directory_iterator dir_begin(const Twine &Dir, std::error_code &EC) override; ----
273 ----
274 llvm::ErrorOr getCurrentWorkingDirectory() const override; ----
275 std::error_code setCurrentWorkingDirectory(const Twine &Path) override; ----
276 std::error_code isLocal(const Twine &Path, bool &Result) override; ----
277 std::error_code getRealPath(const Twine &Path, ----
278 SmallVectorImpl &Output) const override; ----
279 ----
280 protected: ----
281 void printImpl(raw_ostream &OS, PrintType Type, ----
282 unsigned IndentLevel) const override; ----
283 ----
284 private: ----
285 // If this FS has its own working dir, use it to make Path absolute. ----
286 // The returned twine is safe to use as long as both Storage and Path live. ----
287 Twine adjustPath(const Twine &Path, SmallVectorImpl &Storage) const { 0
288 if (!WD || !*WD) 0
289 return Path; 0
290 Path.toVector(Storage); 0
291 sys::fs::make_absolute(WD->get().Resolved, Storage); 0
292 return Storage; 0
293 } ----

295 struct WorkingDirectory { ----
296 // The current working directory, without symlinks resolved. (echo $PWD). ----
297 SmallString<128> Specified; ----
298 // The current working directory, with links resolved. (readlink .). ----
299 SmallString<128> Resolved; ----
300 }; ----
301 std::optional> WD; ----
302 }; ----

339 if (!WD) 0

343 adjustPath(Path, Storage).toVector(Absolute); 0
344 bool IsDir; ----
345 if (auto Err = llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(Absolute, IsDir)) 0
346 return Err; 0

350 return Err; 0

353 } 0

500 /// Combines and deduplicates directory entries across multiple file systems. ----
501 class CombiningDirIterImpl : public llvm::vfs::detail::DirIterImpl { ----
502 using FileSystemPtr = llvm::IntrusiveRefCntPtr; ----
503 ----
504 /// Iterators to combine, processed in reverse order. ----
505 SmallVector IterList; ----
506 /// The iterator currently being traversed. ----
507 directory_iterator CurrentDirIter; ----
508 /// The set of names already returned as entries. ----
509 llvm::StringSet<> SeenNames; ----
510 ----
511 /// Sets \c CurrentDirIter to the next iterator in the list, or leaves it as ----
512 /// is (at its end position) if we've already gone through them all. ----
513 std::error_code incrementIter(bool IsFirstTime) { 0
514 while (!IterList.empty()) { 0
515 CurrentDirIter = IterList.back(); 0
516 IterList.pop_back(); 0
517 if (CurrentDirIter != directory_iterator()) 0
518 break; // found 0
519 } ----
520 ----
521 if (IsFirstTime && CurrentDirIter == directory_iterator()) 0
522 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
523 return {}; 0
524 } ----
525 ----
526 std::error_code incrementDirIter(bool IsFirstTime) { 0
527 assert((IsFirstTime || CurrentDirIter != directory_iterator()) && 0
528 "incrementing past end"); ----
529 std::error_code EC; 0
530 if (!IsFirstTime) 0
531 CurrentDirIter.increment(EC); 0
532 if (!EC && CurrentDirIter == directory_iterator()) 0
533 EC = incrementIter(IsFirstTime); 0
534 return EC; 0
535 } ----
536 ----
537 std::error_code incrementImpl(bool IsFirstTime) { 0
538 while (true) { ----
539 std::error_code EC = incrementDirIter(IsFirstTime); 0
540 if (EC || CurrentDirIter == directory_iterator()) { 0
541 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(); 0
542 return EC; 0
543 } ----
544 CurrentEntry = *CurrentDirIter; 0
545 StringRef Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(CurrentEntry.path()); 0
546 if (SeenNames.insert(Name).second) 0
547 return EC; // name not seen before 0
548 } 0
549 llvm_unreachable("returned above"); ----
550 } ----
551 ----
552 public: ----
553 CombiningDirIterImpl(ArrayRef FileSystems, std::string Dir, 0
554 std::error_code &EC) { 0
555 for (auto FS : FileSystems) { 0
556 std::error_code FEC; 0
557 directory_iterator Iter = FS->dir_begin(Dir, FEC); 0
558 if (FEC && FEC != errc::no_such_file_or_directory) { 0
559 EC = FEC; 0
560 return; 0
561 } ----
562 if (!FEC) 0
563 IterList.push_back(Iter); 0
564 } 0
565 EC = incrementImpl(true); 0
566 } ----
567 ----
568 CombiningDirIterImpl(ArrayRef DirIters, 0
569 std::error_code &EC) ----
570 : IterList(DirIters.begin(), DirIters.end()) { 0
571 EC = incrementImpl(true); 0
572 } 0
573 ----
574 std::error_code increment() override { return incrementImpl(false); } 0
575 }; ----
576 ----
577 } // namespace ----

595 enum InMemoryNodeKind { ----
596 IME_File, ----
597 IME_Directory, ----
598 IME_HardLink, ----
599 IME_SymbolicLink, ----
600 }; ----
601 ----
602 /// The in memory file system is a tree of Nodes. Every node can either be a ----
603 /// file, symlink, hardlink or a directory. ----
604 class InMemoryNode { ----
605 InMemoryNodeKind Kind; ----
606 std::string FileName; ----
607 ----
608 public: ----
609 InMemoryNode(llvm::StringRef FileName, InMemoryNodeKind Kind) 0
610 : Kind(Kind), FileName(std::string(llvm::sys::path::filename(FileName))) { 0
611 } 0
612 virtual ~InMemoryNode() = default; 0
613 ----
614 /// Return the \p Status for this node. \p RequestedName should be the name ----
615 /// through which the caller referred to this node. It will override ----
616 /// \p Status::Name in the return value, to mimic the behavior of \p RealFile. ----
617 virtual Status getStatus(const Twine &RequestedName) const = 0; ----
618 ----
619 /// Get the filename of this node (the name without the directory part). ----
620 StringRef getFileName() const { return FileName; } 0
621 InMemoryNodeKind getKind() const { return Kind; } 0
622 virtual std::string toString(unsigned Indent) const = 0; ----
623 }; ----
624 ----
625 class InMemoryFile : public InMemoryNode { ----
626 Status Stat; ----
627 std::unique_ptr Buffer; ----
628 ----
629 public: ----
630 InMemoryFile(Status Stat, std::unique_ptr Buffer) 0
631 : InMemoryNode(Stat.getName(), IME_File), Stat(std::move(Stat)), 0
632 Buffer(std::move(Buffer)) {} 0
633 ----
634 Status getStatus(const Twine &RequestedName) const override { 0
635 return Status::copyWithNewName(Stat, RequestedName); 0
636 } ----
637 llvm::MemoryBuffer *getBuffer() const { return Buffer.get(); } 0
638 ----
639 std::string toString(unsigned Indent) const override { 0
640 return (std::string(Indent, ' ') + Stat.getName() + "\n").str(); 0
641 } ----
642 ----
643 static bool classof(const InMemoryNode *N) { 0
644 return N->getKind() == IME_File; 0
645 } ----
646 }; ----

652 ----

656 const InMemoryFile &getResolvedFile() const { return ResolvedFile; } 0
657 ----
658 Status getStatus(const Twine &RequestedName) const override { 0
659 return ResolvedFile.getStatus(RequestedName); 0
660 } ----
661 ----
662 std::string toString(unsigned Indent) const override { 0
663 return std::string(Indent, ' ') + "HardLink to -> " + 0
664 ResolvedFile.toString(0); 0
665 } ----
666 ----
667 static bool classof(const InMemoryNode *N) { 0
668 return N->getKind() == IME_HardLink; 0
669 } ----
670 }; ----
671 ----
672 class InMemorySymbolicLink : public InMemoryNode { ----
673 std::string TargetPath; ----
674 Status Stat; ----
675 ----
676 public: ----
677 InMemorySymbolicLink(StringRef Path, StringRef TargetPath, Status Stat) 0
678 : InMemoryNode(Path, IME_SymbolicLink), TargetPath(std::move(TargetPath)), 0
679 Stat(Stat) {} 0
680 ----
681 std::string toString(unsigned Indent) const override { 0
682 return std::string(Indent, ' ') + "SymbolicLink to -> " + TargetPath; 0
683 } ----
684 ----
685 Status getStatus(const Twine &RequestedName) const override { 0
686 return Status::copyWithNewName(Stat, RequestedName); 0
687 } ----
688 ----
689 StringRef getTargetPath() const { return TargetPath; } 0

692 return N->getKind() == IME_SymbolicLink; 0

696 /// Adapt a InMemoryFile for VFS' File interface. The goal is to make ----
697 /// \p InMemoryFileAdaptor mimic as much as possible the behavior of ----
698 /// \p RealFile. ----
699 class InMemoryFileAdaptor : public File { ----
700 const InMemoryFile &Node; ----
701 /// The name to use when returning a Status for this file. ----
702 std::string RequestedName; ----
703 ----
704 public: ----
705 explicit InMemoryFileAdaptor(const InMemoryFile &Node, 0
706 std::string RequestedName) ----
707 : Node(Node), RequestedName(std::move(RequestedName)) {} 0
708 ----
709 llvm::ErrorOr status() override { 0
710 return Node.getStatus(RequestedName); 0
711 } ----
712 ----
713 llvm::ErrorOr> ----
714 getBuffer(const Twine &Name, int64_t FileSize, bool RequiresNullTerminator, 0
715 bool IsVolatile) override { ----
716 llvm::MemoryBuffer *Buf = Node.getBuffer(); 0
717 return llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBuffer( 0
718 Buf->getBuffer(), Buf->getBufferIdentifier(), RequiresNullTerminator); 0
719 } ----
720 ----
721 std::error_code close() override { return {}; } 0
722 ----
723 void setPath(const Twine &Path) override { RequestedName = Path.str(); } 0
724 }; ----
725 } // namespace ----
726 ----
727 class InMemoryDirectory : public InMemoryNode { ----
728 Status Stat; ----
729 std::map> Entries; ----
730 ----
731 public: ----
732 InMemoryDirectory(Status Stat) 0
733 : InMemoryNode(Stat.getName(), IME_Directory), Stat(std::move(Stat)) {} 0
734 ----
735 /// Return the \p Status for this node. \p RequestedName should be the name ----
736 /// through which the caller referred to this node. It will override ----
737 /// \p Status::Name in the return value, to mimic the behavior of \p RealFile. ----
738 Status getStatus(const Twine &RequestedName) const override { 0
739 return Status::copyWithNewName(Stat, RequestedName); 0
740 } ----
741 ----
742 UniqueID getUniqueID() const { return Stat.getUniqueID(); } 0
743 ----
744 InMemoryNode *getChild(StringRef Name) const { 0
745 auto I = Entries.find(Name.str()); 0
746 if (I != Entries.end()) 0
747 return I->second.get(); 0
748 return nullptr; 0
749 } ----
750 ----
751 InMemoryNode *addChild(StringRef Name, std::unique_ptr Child) { 0
752 return Entries.emplace(Name, std::move(Child)).first->second.get(); 0
753 } ----
754 ----
755 using const_iterator = decltype(Entries)::const_iterator; ----
756 ----
757 const_iterator begin() const { return Entries.begin(); } 0
758 const_iterator end() const { return Entries.end(); } 0
759 ----
760 std::string toString(unsigned Indent) const override { 0
761 std::string Result = ----
762 (std::string(Indent, ' ') + Stat.getName() + "\n").str(); 0
763 for (const auto &Entry : Entries) 0
764 Result += Entry.second->toString(Indent + 2); 0
765 return Result; 0
766 } ----
767 ----
768 static bool classof(const InMemoryNode *N) { 0
769 return N->getKind() == IME_Directory; 0
770 } ----
771 }; ----
772 ----
773 } // namespace detail ----
774 ----
775 // The UniqueID of in-memory files is derived from path and content. ----
776 // This avoids difficulties in creating exactly equivalent in-memory FSes, ----
777 // as often needed in multithreaded programs. ----
778 static sys::fs::UniqueID getUniqueID(hash_code Hash) { 0
779 return sys::fs::UniqueID(std::numeric_limits::max(), 0
780 uint64_t(size_t(Hash))); 0
781 } ----
782 static sys::fs::UniqueID getFileID(sys::fs::UniqueID Parent, 0
783 llvm::StringRef Name, ----
784 llvm::StringRef Contents) { ----
785 return getUniqueID(llvm::hash_combine(Parent.getFile(), Name, Contents)); 0
786 } ----
787 static sys::fs::UniqueID getDirectoryID(sys::fs::UniqueID Parent, 0
788 llvm::StringRef Name) { ----
789 return getUniqueID(llvm::hash_combine(Parent.getFile(), Name)); 0
790 } ----
791 ----
792 Status detail::NewInMemoryNodeInfo::makeStatus() const { 0
793 UniqueID UID = ----
794 (Type == sys::fs::file_type::directory_file) 0
795 ? getDirectoryID(DirUID, Name) 0
796 : getFileID(DirUID, Name, Buffer ? Buffer->getBuffer() : ""); 0
797 ----
798 return Status(Path, UID, llvm::sys::toTimePoint(ModificationTime), User, 0
799 Group, Buffer ? Buffer->getBufferSize() : 0, Type, Perms); 0
800 } ----
801 ----
802 InMemoryFileSystem::InMemoryFileSystem(bool UseNormalizedPaths) 0
803 : Root(new detail::InMemoryDirectory( 0
804 Status("", getDirectoryID(llvm::sys::fs::UniqueID(), ""), 0
805 llvm::sys::TimePoint<>(), 0, 0, 0, ----
806 llvm::sys::fs::file_type::directory_file, ----
807 llvm::sys::fs::perms::all_all))), 0
808 UseNormalizedPaths(UseNormalizedPaths) {} 0
809 ----
810 InMemoryFileSystem::~InMemoryFileSystem() = default; 0
811 ----
812 std::string InMemoryFileSystem::toString() const { 0
813 return Root->toString(/*Indent=*/0); 0
814 } ----
815 ----
816 bool InMemoryFileSystem::addFile(const Twine &P, time_t ModificationTime, 0
817 std::unique_ptr Buffer, ----
818 std::optional User, ----
819 std::optional Group, ----
820 std::optional Type, ----
821 std::optional Perms, ----
822 MakeNodeFn MakeNode) { ----
823 SmallString<128> Path; 0
824 P.toVector(Path); 0
825 ----
826 // Fix up relative paths. This just prepends the current working directory. ----
827 std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(Path); 0
828 assert(!EC); 0
829 (void)EC; ----
830 ----
831 if (useNormalizedPaths()) 0
832 llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(Path, /*remove_dot_dot=*/true); 0
833 ----
834 if (Path.empty()) 0
835 return false; 0
836 ----
837 detail::InMemoryDirectory *Dir = Root.get(); 0
838 auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(Path), E = sys::path::end(Path); 0
839 const auto ResolvedUser = User.value_or(0); 0
840 const auto ResolvedGroup = Group.value_or(0); 0
841 const auto ResolvedType = Type.value_or(sys::fs::file_type::regular_file); 0
842 const auto ResolvedPerms = Perms.value_or(sys::fs::all_all); 0
843 // Any intermediate directories we create should be accessible by ----
844 // the owner, even if Perms says otherwise for the final path. ----
845 const auto NewDirectoryPerms = ResolvedPerms | sys::fs::owner_all; 0
846 while (true) { ----
847 StringRef Name = *I; 0
848 detail::InMemoryNode *Node = Dir->getChild(Name); 0
849 ++I; 0
850 if (!Node) { 0
851 if (I == E) { 0
852 // End of the path. ----
853 Dir->addChild( 0
854 Name, MakeNode({Dir->getUniqueID(), Path, Name, ModificationTime, 0
855 std::move(Buffer), ResolvedUser, ResolvedGroup, 0
856 ResolvedType, ResolvedPerms})); ----
857 return true; 0
858 } ----
859 ----
860 // Create a new directory. Use the path up to here. ----
861 Status Stat( ----
862 StringRef(Path.str().begin(), Name.end() - Path.str().begin()), 0
863 getDirectoryID(Dir->getUniqueID(), Name), ----
864 llvm::sys::toTimePoint(ModificationTime), ResolvedUser, ResolvedGroup, 0
865 0, sys::fs::file_type::directory_file, NewDirectoryPerms); 0
866 Dir = cast(Dir->addChild( 0
867 Name, std::make_unique(std::move(Stat)))); 0
868 continue; 0
869 } 0
870 ----
871 if (auto *NewDir = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
872 Dir = NewDir; 0
873 } else { ----
874 assert((isa(Node) || 0
875 isa(Node)) && ----
876 "Must be either file, hardlink or directory!"); ----
877 ----
878 // Trying to insert a directory in place of a file. ----
879 if (I != E) 0
880 return false; 0
881 ----
882 // Return false only if the new file is different from the existing one. ----
883 if (auto Link = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
884 return Link->getResolvedFile().getBuffer()->getBuffer() == 0
885 Buffer->getBuffer(); 0
886 } ----
887 return cast(Node)->getBuffer()->getBuffer() == 0
888 Buffer->getBuffer(); 0
889 } ----
890 } 0
891 } 0
892 ----
893 bool InMemoryFileSystem::addFile(const Twine &P, time_t ModificationTime, 0
894 std::unique_ptr Buffer, ----
895 std::optional User, ----
896 std::optional Group, ----
897 std::optional Type, ----
898 std::optional Perms) { ----
899 return addFile(P, ModificationTime, std::move(Buffer), User, Group, Type, 0
900 Perms, ----
901 [](detail::NewInMemoryNodeInfo NNI) 0
902 -> std::unique_ptr { ----
903 Status Stat = NNI.makeStatus(); 0
904 if (Stat.getType() == sys::fs::file_type::directory_file) 0
905 return std::make_unique(Stat); 0
906 return std::make_unique( 0
907 Stat, std::move(NNI.Buffer)); 0
908 }); 0
909 } ----
910 ----
911 bool InMemoryFileSystem::addFileNoOwn( 0
912 const Twine &P, time_t ModificationTime, ----
913 const llvm::MemoryBufferRef &Buffer, std::optional User, ----
914 std::optional Group, std::optional Type, ----
915 std::optional Perms) { ----
916 return addFile(P, ModificationTime, llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBuffer(Buffer), 0
917 std::move(User), std::move(Group), std::move(Type), 0
918 std::move(Perms), 0
919 [](detail::NewInMemoryNodeInfo NNI) 0
920 -> std::unique_ptr { ----
921 Status Stat = NNI.makeStatus(); 0
922 if (Stat.getType() == sys::fs::file_type::directory_file) 0
923 return std::make_unique(Stat); 0
924 return std::make_unique( 0
925 Stat, std::move(NNI.Buffer)); 0
926 }); 0
927 } ----
928 ----
929 detail::NamedNodeOrError ----
930 InMemoryFileSystem::lookupNode(const Twine &P, bool FollowFinalSymlink, 0
931 size_t SymlinkDepth) const { ----
932 SmallString<128> Path; 0
933 P.toVector(Path); 0
934 ----
935 // Fix up relative paths. This just prepends the current working directory. ----
936 std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(Path); 0
937 assert(!EC); 0
938 (void)EC; ----
939 ----
940 if (useNormalizedPaths()) 0
941 llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(Path, /*remove_dot_dot=*/true); 0
942 ----
943 const detail::InMemoryDirectory *Dir = Root.get(); 0
944 if (Path.empty()) 0
945 return detail::NamedNodeOrError(Path, Dir); 0
946 ----
947 auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(Path), E = llvm::sys::path::end(Path); 0
948 while (true) { ----
949 detail::InMemoryNode *Node = Dir->getChild(*I); 0
950 ++I; 0
951 if (!Node) 0
952 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
953 ----
954 if (auto Symlink = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
955 // If we're at the end of the path, and we're not following through ----
956 // terminal symlinks, then we're done. ----
957 if (I == E && !FollowFinalSymlink) 0
958 return detail::NamedNodeOrError(Path, Symlink); 0
959 ----
960 if (SymlinkDepth > InMemoryFileSystem::MaxSymlinkDepth) 0
961 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
962 ----
963 SmallString<128> TargetPath = Symlink->getTargetPath(); 0
964 if (std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(TargetPath)) 0
965 return EC; 0
966 ----
967 // Keep going with the target. We always want to follow symlinks here ----
968 // because we're either at the end of a path that we want to follow, or ----
969 // not at the end of a path, in which case we need to follow the symlink ----
970 // regardless. ----
971 auto Target = ----
972 lookupNode(TargetPath, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true, SymlinkDepth + 1); 0
973 if (!Target || I == E) 0
974 return Target; 0
975 ----
976 if (!isa(*Target)) 0
977 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
978 ----
979 // Otherwise, continue on the search in the symlinked directory. ----
980 Dir = cast(*Target); 0
981 continue; 0
982 } 0
983 ----
984 // Return the file if it's at the end of the path. ----
985 if (auto File = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
986 if (I == E) 0
987 return detail::NamedNodeOrError(Path, File); 0
988 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
989 } ----
990 ----
991 // If Node is HardLink then return the resolved file. ----
992 if (auto File = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
993 if (I == E) 0
994 return detail::NamedNodeOrError(Path, &File->getResolvedFile()); 0
995 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
996 } ----
997 // Traverse directories. ----
998 Dir = cast(Node); 0
999 if (I == E) 0
1000 return detail::NamedNodeOrError(Path, Dir); 0
1001 } 0
1002 } 0
1003 ----
1004 bool InMemoryFileSystem::addHardLink(const Twine &NewLink, 0
1005 const Twine &Target) { ----
1006 auto NewLinkNode = lookupNode(NewLink, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/false); 0
1007 // Whether symlinks in the hardlink target are followed is ----
1008 // implementation-defined in POSIX. ----
1009 // We're following symlinks here to be consistent with macOS. ----
1010 auto TargetNode = lookupNode(Target, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true); 0
1011 // FromPath must not have been added before. ToPath must have been added ----
1012 // before. Resolved ToPath must be a File. ----
1013 if (!TargetNode || NewLinkNode || !isa(*TargetNode)) 0
1014 return false; 0
1015 return addFile(NewLink, 0, nullptr, std::nullopt, std::nullopt, std::nullopt, 0
1016 std::nullopt, [&](detail::NewInMemoryNodeInfo NNI) { 0
1017 return std::make_unique( ----
1018 NNI.Path.str(), 0
1019 *cast(*TargetNode)); 0
1020 }); 0
1021 } 0
1022 ----
1023 bool InMemoryFileSystem::addSymbolicLink( 0
1024 const Twine &NewLink, const Twine &Target, time_t ModificationTime, ----
1025 std::optional User, std::optional Group, ----
1026 std::optional Perms) { ----
1027 auto NewLinkNode = lookupNode(NewLink, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/false); 0
1028 if (NewLinkNode) 0
1029 return false; 0
1030 ----
1031 SmallString<128> NewLinkStr, TargetStr; 0
1032 NewLink.toVector(NewLinkStr); 0
1033 Target.toVector(TargetStr); 0
1034 ----
1035 return addFile(NewLinkStr, ModificationTime, nullptr, User, Group, 0
1036 sys::fs::file_type::symlink_file, Perms, 0
1037 [&](detail::NewInMemoryNodeInfo NNI) { 0
1038 return std::make_unique( ----
1039 NewLinkStr, TargetStr, NNI.makeStatus()); 0
1040 }); 0
1041 } 0
1042 ----
1043 llvm::ErrorOr InMemoryFileSystem::status(const Twine &Path) { 0
1044 auto Node = lookupNode(Path, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true); 0
1045 if (Node) 0
1046 return (*Node)->getStatus(Path); 0
1047 return Node.getError(); 0
1048 } 0
1049 ----
1050 llvm::ErrorOr> ----
1051 InMemoryFileSystem::openFileForRead(const Twine &Path) { 0
1052 auto Node = lookupNode(Path,/*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true); 0
1053 if (!Node) 0
1054 return Node.getError(); 0
1055 ----
1056 // When we have a file provide a heap-allocated wrapper for the memory buffer ----
1057 // to match the ownership semantics for File. ----
1058 if (auto *F = dyn_cast(*Node)) 0
1059 return std::unique_ptr( 0
1060 new detail::InMemoryFileAdaptor(*F, Path.str())); 0
1061 ----
1062 // FIXME: errc::not_a_file? ----
1063 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::invalid_argument); 0
1064 } 0
1065 ----
1066 /// Adaptor from InMemoryDir::iterator to directory_iterator. ----
1067 class InMemoryFileSystem::DirIterator : public llvm::vfs::detail::DirIterImpl { ----
1068 const InMemoryFileSystem *FS; ----
1069 detail::InMemoryDirectory::const_iterator I; ----
1070 detail::InMemoryDirectory::const_iterator E; ----
1071 std::string RequestedDirName; ----
1072 ----
1073 void setCurrentEntry() { 0
1074 if (I != E) { 0
1075 SmallString<256> Path(RequestedDirName); 0
1076 llvm::sys::path::append(Path, I->second->getFileName()); 0
1077 sys::fs::file_type Type = sys::fs::file_type::type_unknown; 0
1078 switch (I->second->getKind()) { 0
1079 case detail::IME_File: 0
1080 case detail::IME_HardLink: ----
1081 Type = sys::fs::file_type::regular_file; 0
1082 break; 0
1083 case detail::IME_Directory: 0
1084 Type = sys::fs::file_type::directory_file; 0
1085 break; 0
1086 case detail::IME_SymbolicLink: 0
1087 if (auto SymlinkTarget = 0
1088 FS->lookupNode(Path, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true)) { 0
1089 Path = SymlinkTarget.getName(); 0
1090 Type = (*SymlinkTarget)->getStatus(Path).getType(); 0
1091 } 0
1092 break; 0
1093 } ----
1094 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(std::string(Path.str()), Type); 0
1095 } else { 0
1096 // When we're at the end, make CurrentEntry invalid and DirIterImpl will ----
1097 // do the rest. ----
1098 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(); 0
1099 } ----
1100 } 0
1101 ----
1102 public: ----
1103 DirIterator() = default; 0
1104 ----
1105 DirIterator(const InMemoryFileSystem *FS, 0
1106 const detail::InMemoryDirectory &Dir, ----
1107 std::string RequestedDirName) ----
1108 : FS(FS), I(Dir.begin()), E(Dir.end()), 0
1109 RequestedDirName(std::move(RequestedDirName)) { 0
1110 setCurrentEntry(); 0
1111 } 0
1112 ----
1113 std::error_code increment() override { 0
1114 ++I; 0
1115 setCurrentEntry(); 0
1116 return {}; 0
1117 } ----
1118 }; ----
1119 ----
1120 directory_iterator InMemoryFileSystem::dir_begin(const Twine &Dir, 0
1121 std::error_code &EC) { ----
1122 auto Node = lookupNode(Dir, /*FollowFinalSymlink=*/true); 0
1123 if (!Node) { 0
1124 EC = Node.getError(); 0
1125 return directory_iterator(std::make_shared()); 0
1126 } ----
1127 ----
1128 if (auto *DirNode = dyn_cast(*Node)) 0
1129 return directory_iterator( ----
1130 std::make_shared(this, *DirNode, Dir.str())); 0
1131 ----
1132 EC = make_error_code(llvm::errc::not_a_directory); 0
1133 return directory_iterator(std::make_shared()); 0
1134 } 0
1135 ----
1136 std::error_code InMemoryFileSystem::setCurrentWorkingDirectory(const Twine &P) { 0
1137 SmallString<128> Path; 0
1138 P.toVector(Path); 0
1139 ----
1140 // Fix up relative paths. This just prepends the current working directory. ----
1141 std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(Path); 0
1142 assert(!EC); 0
1143 (void)EC; ----
1144 ----
1145 if (useNormalizedPaths()) 0
1146 llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(Path, /*remove_dot_dot=*/true); 0
1147 ----
1148 if (!Path.empty()) 0
1149 WorkingDirectory = std::string(Path.str()); 0
1150 return {}; 0
1151 } 0
1152 ----
1153 std::error_code ----
1154 InMemoryFileSystem::getRealPath(const Twine &Path, 0
1155 SmallVectorImpl &Output) const { ----
1156 auto CWD = getCurrentWorkingDirectory(); 0
1157 if (!CWD || CWD->empty()) 0
1158 return errc::operation_not_permitted; 0
1159 Path.toVector(Output); 0
1160 if (auto EC = makeAbsolute(Output)) 0
1161 return EC; 0
1162 llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(Output, /*remove_dot_dot=*/true); 0
1163 return {}; 0
1164 } 0

1166 std::error_code InMemoryFileSystem::isLocal(const Twine &Path, bool &Result) { 0
1167 Result = false; 0
1168 return {}; 0
1169 } ----

1186 static llvm::sys::path::Style getExistingStyle(llvm::StringRef Path) { 0
1187 // Detect the path style in use by checking the first separator. ----
1188 llvm::sys::path::Style style = llvm::sys::path::Style::native; 0
1189 const size_t n = Path.find_first_of("/\\"); 0
1190 // Can't distinguish between posix and windows_slash here. ----
1191 if (n != static_cast(-1)) 0
1192 style = (Path[n] == '/') ? llvm::sys::path::Style::posix 0
1193 : llvm::sys::path::Style::windows_backslash; ----
1194 return style; 0
1195 } ----
1196 ----
1197 /// Removes leading "./" as well as path components like ".." and ".". ----
1198 static llvm::SmallString<256> canonicalize(llvm::StringRef Path) { 0
1199 // First detect the path style in use by checking the first separator. ----
1200 llvm::sys::path::Style style = getExistingStyle(Path); 0
1201 ----
1202 // Now remove the dots. Explicitly specifying the path style prevents the ----
1203 // direction of the slashes from changing. ----
1204 llvm::SmallString<256> result = ----
1205 llvm::sys::path::remove_leading_dotslash(Path, style); 0
1206 llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(result, /*remove_dot_dot=*/true, style); 0
1207 return result; 0
1208 } ----
1209 ----
1210 /// Whether the error and entry specify a file/directory that was not found. ----
1211 static bool isFileNotFound(std::error_code EC, 0
1212 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *E = nullptr) { ----
1213 if (E && !isa(E)) 0
1214 return false; 0
1215 return EC == llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
1216 } ----
1217 ----
1218 } // anonymous namespace ----

1221 RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectingFileSystem(IntrusiveRefCntPtr FS) 0
1222 : ExternalFS(std::move(FS)) { 0
1223 if (ExternalFS) 0
1224 if (auto ExternalWorkingDirectory = 0
1225 ExternalFS->getCurrentWorkingDirectory()) { 0
1226 WorkingDirectory = *ExternalWorkingDirectory; 0
1227 } 0
1228 } 0

1230 /// Directory iterator implementation for \c RedirectingFileSystem's ----
1231 /// directory entries. ----
1232 class llvm::vfs::RedirectingFSDirIterImpl ----
1233 : public llvm::vfs::detail::DirIterImpl { ----
1234 std::string Dir; ----
1235 RedirectingFileSystem::DirectoryEntry::iterator Current, End; ----
1236 ----
1237 std::error_code incrementImpl(bool IsFirstTime) { 0
1238 assert((IsFirstTime || Current != End) && "cannot iterate past end"); 0
1239 if (!IsFirstTime) 0
1240 ++Current; 0
1241 if (Current != End) { 0
1242 SmallString<128> PathStr(Dir); 0
1243 llvm::sys::path::append(PathStr, (*Current)->getName()); 0
1244 sys::fs::file_type Type = sys::fs::file_type::type_unknown; 0
1245 switch ((*Current)->getKind()) { 0
1246 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_Directory: 0
1247 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1248 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_DirectoryRemap: ----
1249 Type = sys::fs::file_type::directory_file; 0
1250 break; 0
1251 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_File: 0
1252 Type = sys::fs::file_type::regular_file; 0
1253 break; 0
1254 } ----
1255 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(std::string(PathStr.str()), Type); 0
1256 } else { 0
1257 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(); 0
1258 } ----
1259 return {}; 0
1260 }; ----
1261 ----
1262 public: ----
1263 RedirectingFSDirIterImpl( 0
1264 const Twine &Path, RedirectingFileSystem::DirectoryEntry::iterator Begin, ----
1265 RedirectingFileSystem::DirectoryEntry::iterator End, std::error_code &EC) ----
1266 : Dir(Path.str()), Current(Begin), End(End) { 0
1267 EC = incrementImpl(/*IsFirstTime=*/true); 0
1268 } 0
1269 ----
1270 std::error_code increment() override { 0
1271 return incrementImpl(/*IsFirstTime=*/false); 0
1272 } ----
1273 }; ----

1275 namespace { ----
1276 /// Directory iterator implementation for \c RedirectingFileSystem's ----
1277 /// directory remap entries that maps the paths reported by the external ----
1278 /// file system's directory iterator back to the virtual directory's path. ----
1279 class RedirectingFSDirRemapIterImpl : public llvm::vfs::detail::DirIterImpl { ----
1280 std::string Dir; ----
1281 llvm::sys::path::Style DirStyle; ----
1282 llvm::vfs::directory_iterator ExternalIter; ----
1283 ----
1284 public: ----
1285 RedirectingFSDirRemapIterImpl(std::string DirPath, 0
1286 llvm::vfs::directory_iterator ExtIter) ----
1287 : Dir(std::move(DirPath)), DirStyle(getExistingStyle(Dir)), 0
1288 ExternalIter(ExtIter) { 0
1289 if (ExternalIter != llvm::vfs::directory_iterator()) 0
1290 setCurrentEntry(); 0
1291 } 0
1292 ----
1293 void setCurrentEntry() { 0
1294 StringRef ExternalPath = ExternalIter->path(); 0
1295 llvm::sys::path::Style ExternalStyle = getExistingStyle(ExternalPath); 0
1296 StringRef File = llvm::sys::path::filename(ExternalPath, ExternalStyle); 0
1297 ----
1298 SmallString<128> NewPath(Dir); 0
1299 llvm::sys::path::append(NewPath, DirStyle, File); 0
1300 ----
1301 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(std::string(NewPath), ExternalIter->type()); 0
1302 } 0
1303 ----
1304 std::error_code increment() override { 0
1305 std::error_code EC; 0
1306 ExternalIter.increment(EC); 0
1307 if (!EC && ExternalIter != llvm::vfs::directory_iterator()) 0
1308 setCurrentEntry(); 0
1309 else ----
1310 CurrentEntry = directory_entry(); 0
1311 return EC; 0
1312 } ----
1313 }; ----
1314 } // namespace ----

1316 llvm::ErrorOr ----
1317 RedirectingFileSystem::getCurrentWorkingDirectory() const { 0
1318 return WorkingDirectory; 0
1319 } ----
1320 ----
1321 std::error_code ----
1322 RedirectingFileSystem::setCurrentWorkingDirectory(const Twine &Path) { 0
1323 // Don't change the working directory if the path doesn't exist. ----
1324 if (!exists(Path)) 0
1325 return errc::no_such_file_or_directory; 0
1326 ----
1327 SmallString<128> AbsolutePath; 0
1328 Path.toVector(AbsolutePath); 0
1329 if (std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(AbsolutePath)) 0
1330 return EC; 0
1331 WorkingDirectory = std::string(AbsolutePath.str()); 0
1332 return {}; 0
1333 } 0
1334 ----
1335 std::error_code RedirectingFileSystem::isLocal(const Twine &Path_, 0
1336 bool &Result) { ----
1337 SmallString<256> Path; 0
1338 Path_.toVector(Path); 0
1339 ----
1340 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(Path)) 0
1341 return {}; 0
1342 ----
1343 return ExternalFS->isLocal(Path, Result); 0
1344 } 0
1345 ----
1346 std::error_code RedirectingFileSystem::makeAbsolute(SmallVectorImpl &Path) const { 0
1347 // is_absolute(..., Style::windows_*) accepts paths with both slash types. ----
1348 if (llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(Path, llvm::sys::path::Style::posix) || 0
1349 llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(Path, 0
1350 llvm::sys::path::Style::windows_backslash)) ----
1351 // This covers windows absolute path with forward slash as well, as the ----
1352 // forward slashes are treated as path seperation in llvm::path ----
1353 // regardless of what path::Style is used. ----
1354 return {}; 0
1355 ----
1356 auto WorkingDir = getCurrentWorkingDirectory(); 0
1357 if (!WorkingDir) 0
1358 return WorkingDir.getError(); 0
1359 ----
1360 return makeAbsolute(WorkingDir.get(), Path); 0
1361 } 0
1362 ----
1363 std::error_code ----
1364 RedirectingFileSystem::makeAbsolute(StringRef WorkingDir, 0
1365 SmallVectorImpl &Path) const { ----
1366 // We can't use sys::fs::make_absolute because that assumes the path style ----
1367 // is native and there is no way to override that. Since we know WorkingDir ----
1368 // is absolute, we can use it to determine which style we actually have and ----
1369 // append Path ourselves. ----
1370 if (!WorkingDir.empty() && 0
1371 !sys::path::is_absolute(WorkingDir, sys::path::Style::posix) && 0
1372 !sys::path::is_absolute(WorkingDir, 0
1373 sys::path::Style::windows_backslash)) { ----
1374 return std::error_code(); 0
1375 } ----
1376 sys::path::Style style = sys::path::Style::windows_backslash; 0
1377 if (sys::path::is_absolute(WorkingDir, sys::path::Style::posix)) { 0
1378 style = sys::path::Style::posix; 0
1379 } else { ----
1380 // Distinguish between windows_backslash and windows_slash; getExistingStyle ----
1381 // returns posix for a path with windows_slash. ----
1382 if (getExistingStyle(WorkingDir) != sys::path::Style::windows_backslash) 0
1383 style = sys::path::Style::windows_slash; 0
1384 } ----
1385 ----
1386 std::string Result = std::string(WorkingDir); 0
1387 StringRef Dir(Result); 0
1388 if (!Dir.endswith(sys::path::get_separator(style))) { 0
1389 Result += sys::path::get_separator(style); 0
1390 } ----
1391 // backslashes '\' are legit path charactors under POSIX. Windows APIs ----
1392 // like CreateFile accepts forward slashes '/' as path ----
1393 // separator (even when mixed with backslashes). Therefore, ----
1394 // `Path` should be directly appended to `WorkingDir` without converting ----
1395 // path separator. ----
1396 Result.append(Path.data(), Path.size()); 0
1397 Path.assign(Result.begin(), Result.end()); 0
1398 ----
1399 return {}; 0
1400 } 0
1401 ----
1402 directory_iterator RedirectingFileSystem::dir_begin(const Twine &Dir, 0
1403 std::error_code &EC) { ----
1404 SmallString<256> Path; 0
1405 Dir.toVector(Path); 0
1406 ----
1407 EC = makeCanonical(Path); 0
1408 if (EC) 0
1409 return {}; 0
1410 ----
1411 ErrorOr Result = lookupPath(Path); 0
1412 if (!Result) { 0
1413 if (Redirection != RedirectKind::RedirectOnly && 0
1414 isFileNotFound(Result.getError())) 0
1415 return ExternalFS->dir_begin(Path, EC); 0
1416 ----
1417 EC = Result.getError(); 0
1418 return {}; 0
1419 } ----
1420 ----
1421 // Use status to make sure the path exists and refers to a directory. ----
1422 ErrorOr S = status(Path, Dir, *Result); 0
1423 if (!S) { 0
1424 if (Redirection != RedirectKind::RedirectOnly && 0
1425 isFileNotFound(S.getError(), Result->E)) 0
1426 return ExternalFS->dir_begin(Dir, EC); 0
1427 ----
1428 EC = S.getError(); 0
1429 return {}; 0
1430 } ----
1431 ----
1432 if (!S->isDirectory()) { 0
1433 EC = errc::not_a_directory; 0
1434 return {}; 0
1435 } ----
1436 ----
1437 // Create the appropriate directory iterator based on whether we found a ----
1438 // DirectoryRemapEntry or DirectoryEntry. ----
1439 directory_iterator RedirectIter; 0
1440 std::error_code RedirectEC; 0
1441 if (auto ExtRedirect = Result->getExternalRedirect()) { 0
1442 auto RE = cast(Result->E); 0
1443 RedirectIter = ExternalFS->dir_begin(*ExtRedirect, RedirectEC); 0
1444 ----
1445 if (!RE->useExternalName(UseExternalNames)) { 0
1446 // Update the paths in the results to use the virtual directory's path. ----
1447 RedirectIter = ----
1448 directory_iterator(std::make_shared( 0
1449 std::string(Path), RedirectIter)); 0
1450 } ----
1451 } else { ----
1452 auto DE = cast(Result->E); 0
1453 RedirectIter = ----
1454 directory_iterator(std::make_shared( 0
1455 Path, DE->contents_begin(), DE->contents_end(), RedirectEC)); 0
1456 } ----
1457 ----
1458 if (RedirectEC) { 0
1459 if (RedirectEC != errc::no_such_file_or_directory) { 0
1460 EC = RedirectEC; 0
1461 return {}; 0
1462 } ----
1463 RedirectIter = {}; 0
1464 } ----
1465 ----
1466 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::RedirectOnly) { 0
1467 EC = RedirectEC; 0
1468 return RedirectIter; 0
1469 } ----
1470 ----
1471 std::error_code ExternalEC; 0
1472 directory_iterator ExternalIter = ExternalFS->dir_begin(Path, ExternalEC); 0
1473 if (ExternalEC) { 0
1474 if (ExternalEC != errc::no_such_file_or_directory) { 0
1475 EC = ExternalEC; 0
1476 return {}; 0
1477 } ----
1478 ExternalIter = {}; 0
1479 } ----
1480 ----
1481 SmallVector Iters; 0
1482 switch (Redirection) { 0
1483 case RedirectKind::Fallthrough: 0
1484 Iters.push_back(ExternalIter); 0
1485 Iters.push_back(RedirectIter); 0
1486 break; 0
1487 case RedirectKind::Fallback: 0
1488 Iters.push_back(RedirectIter); 0
1489 Iters.push_back(ExternalIter); 0
1490 break; 0
1491 default: 0
1492 llvm_unreachable("unhandled RedirectKind"); 0
1493 } ----
1494 ----
1495 directory_iterator Combined{ ----
1496 std::make_shared(Iters, EC)}; 0
1497 if (EC) 0
1498 return {}; 0
1499 return Combined; 0
1500 } 0

1503 OverlayFileDir = Dir.str(); 0
1504 } 0

1506 StringRef RedirectingFileSystem::getOverlayFileDir() const { 0
1507 return OverlayFileDir; 0
1508 } ----

1510 void RedirectingFileSystem::setFallthrough(bool Fallthrough) { 0
1511 if (Fallthrough) { 0
1512 Redirection = RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::Fallthrough; 0
1513 } else { ----
1514 Redirection = RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::RedirectOnly; 0
1515 } ----
1516 } 0

1520 Redirection = Kind; 0
1521 } 0
1522 ----
1523 std::vector RedirectingFileSystem::getRoots() const { 0
1524 std::vector R; 0
1525 R.reserve(Roots.size()); 0
1526 for (const auto &Root : Roots) 0
1527 R.push_back(Root->getName()); 0
1528 return R; 0
1529 } ----
1530 ----
1531 void RedirectingFileSystem::printImpl(raw_ostream &OS, PrintType Type, 0
1532 unsigned IndentLevel) const { ----
1533 printIndent(OS, IndentLevel); 0
1534 OS << "RedirectingFileSystem (UseExternalNames: " 0
1535 << (UseExternalNames ? "true" : "false") << ")\n"; 0
1536 if (Type == PrintType::Summary) 0
1537 return; 0
1538 ----
1539 for (const auto &Root : Roots) 0
1540 printEntry(OS, Root.get(), IndentLevel); 0
1541 ----
1542 printIndent(OS, IndentLevel); 0
1543 OS << "ExternalFS:\n"; 0
1544 ExternalFS->print(OS, Type == PrintType::Contents ? PrintType::Summary : Type, 0
1545 IndentLevel + 1); ----
1546 } ----
1547 ----
1548 void RedirectingFileSystem::printEntry(raw_ostream &OS, 0
1549 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *E, ----
1550 unsigned IndentLevel) const { ----
1551 printIndent(OS, IndentLevel); 0
1552 OS << "'" << E->getName() << "'"; 0
1553 ----
1554 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
1555 case EK_Directory: { 0
1556 auto *DE = cast(E); 0
1557 ----
1558 OS << "\n"; 0
1559 for (std::unique_ptr &SubEntry : 0
1560 llvm::make_range(DE->contents_begin(), DE->contents_end())) 0
1561 printEntry(OS, SubEntry.get(), IndentLevel + 1); 0
1562 break; 0
1563 } ----
1564 case EK_DirectoryRemap: 0
1565 case EK_File: { ----
1566 auto *RE = cast(E); 0
1567 OS << " -> '" << RE->getExternalContentsPath() << "'"; 0
1568 switch (RE->getUseName()) { 0
1569 case NK_NotSet: 0
1570 break; 0
1571 case NK_External: 0
1572 OS << " (UseExternalName: true)"; 0
1573 break; 0
1574 case NK_Virtual: 0
1575 OS << " (UseExternalName: false)"; 0
1576 break; 0
1577 } ----
1578 OS << "\n"; 0
1579 break; 0
1580 } ----
1581 } ----
1582 } 0
1583 ----
1584 /// A helper class to hold the common YAML parsing state. ----
1585 class llvm::vfs::RedirectingFileSystemParser { ----
1586 yaml::Stream &Stream; ----
1587 ----
1588 void error(yaml::Node *N, const Twine &Msg) { Stream.printError(N, Msg); } 0
1589 ----
1590 // false on error ----
1591 bool parseScalarString(yaml::Node *N, StringRef &Result, 0
1592 SmallVectorImpl &Storage) { ----
1593 const auto *S = dyn_cast(N); 0
1594 ----
1595 if (!S) { 0
1596 error(N, "expected string"); 0
1597 return false; 0
1598 } ----
1599 Result = S->getValue(Storage); 0
1600 return true; 0
1601 } ----
1602 ----
1603 // false on error ----
1604 bool parseScalarBool(yaml::Node *N, bool &Result) { 0
1605 SmallString<5> Storage; 0
1606 StringRef Value; 0
1607 if (!parseScalarString(N, Value, Storage)) 0
1608 return false; 0
1609 ----
1610 if (Value.equals_insensitive("true") || Value.equals_insensitive("on") || 0
1611 Value.equals_insensitive("yes") || Value == "1") { 0
1612 Result = true; 0
1613 return true; 0
1614 } else if (Value.equals_insensitive("false") || 0
1615 Value.equals_insensitive("off") || 0
1616 Value.equals_insensitive("no") || Value == "0") { 0
1617 Result = false; 0
1618 return true; 0
1619 } ----
1620 ----
1621 error(N, "expected boolean value"); 0
1622 return false; 0
1623 } 0
1624 ----
1625 std::optional ----
1626 parseRedirectKind(yaml::Node *N) { 0
1627 SmallString<12> Storage; 0
1628 StringRef Value; 0
1629 if (!parseScalarString(N, Value, Storage)) 0
1630 return std::nullopt; 0
1631 ----
1632 if (Value.equals_insensitive("fallthrough")) { 0
1633 return RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::Fallthrough; 0
1634 } else if (Value.equals_insensitive("fallback")) { 0
1635 return RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::Fallback; 0
1636 } else if (Value.equals_insensitive("redirect-only")) { 0
1637 return RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::RedirectOnly; 0
1638 } ----
1639 return std::nullopt; 0
1640 } 0
1641 ----
1642 std::optional ----
1643 parseRootRelativeKind(yaml::Node *N) { 0
1644 SmallString<12> Storage; 0
1645 StringRef Value; 0
1646 if (!parseScalarString(N, Value, Storage)) 0
1647 return std::nullopt; 0
1648 if (Value.equals_insensitive("cwd")) { 0
1649 return RedirectingFileSystem::RootRelativeKind::CWD; 0
1650 } else if (Value.equals_insensitive("overlay-dir")) { 0
1651 return RedirectingFileSystem::RootRelativeKind::OverlayDir; 0
1652 } ----
1653 return std::nullopt; 0
1654 } 0
1655 ----
1656 struct KeyStatus { ----
1657 bool Required; ----
1658 bool Seen = false; ----
1659 ----
1660 KeyStatus(bool Required = false) : Required(Required) {} 0
1661 }; ----
1662 ----
1663 using KeyStatusPair = std::pair; ----
1664 ----
1665 // false on error ----
1666 bool checkDuplicateOrUnknownKey(yaml::Node *KeyNode, StringRef Key, 0
1667 DenseMap &Keys) { ----
1668 if (!Keys.count(Key)) { 0
1669 error(KeyNode, "unknown key"); 0
1670 return false; 0
1671 } ----
1672 KeyStatus &S = Keys[Key]; 0
1673 if (S.Seen) { 0
1674 error(KeyNode, Twine("duplicate key '") + Key + "'"); 0
1675 return false; 0
1676 } ----
1677 S.Seen = true; 0
1678 return true; 0
1679 } ----
1680 ----
1681 // false on error ----
1682 bool checkMissingKeys(yaml::Node *Obj, DenseMap &Keys) { 0
1683 for (const auto &I : Keys) { 0
1684 if (I.second.Required && !I.second.Seen) { 0
1685 error(Obj, Twine("missing key '") + I.first + "'"); 0
1686 return false; 0
1687 } ----
1688 } ----
1689 return true; 0
1690 } ----
1691 ----
1692 public: ----
1693 static RedirectingFileSystem::Entry * ----
1694 lookupOrCreateEntry(RedirectingFileSystem *FS, StringRef Name, 0
1695 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *ParentEntry = nullptr) { ----
1696 if (!ParentEntry) { // Look for a existent root 0
1697 for (const auto &Root : FS->Roots) { 0
1698 if (Name.equals(Root->getName())) { 0
1699 ParentEntry = Root.get(); 0
1700 return ParentEntry; 0
1701 } ----
1702 } ----
1703 } else { // Advance to the next component ----
1704 auto *DE = dyn_cast(ParentEntry); 0
1705 for (std::unique_ptr &Content : 0
1706 llvm::make_range(DE->contents_begin(), DE->contents_end())) { 0
1707 auto *DirContent = ----
1708 dyn_cast(Content.get()); 0
1709 if (DirContent && Name.equals(Content->getName())) 0
1710 return DirContent; 0
1711 } ----
1712 } ----
1713 ----
1714 // ... or create a new one ----
1715 std::unique_ptr E = ----
1716 std::make_unique( 0
1717 Name, Status("", getNextVirtualUniqueID(), 0
1718 std::chrono::system_clock::now(), 0, 0, 0, ----
1719 file_type::directory_file, sys::fs::all_all)); 0
1720 ----
1721 if (!ParentEntry) { // Add a new root to the overlay 0
1722 FS->Roots.push_back(std::move(E)); 0
1723 ParentEntry = FS->Roots.back().get(); 0
1724 return ParentEntry; 0
1725 } ----
1726 ----
1727 auto *DE = cast(ParentEntry); 0
1728 DE->addContent(std::move(E)); 0
1729 return DE->getLastContent(); 0
1730 } 0
1731 ----
1732 private: ----
1733 void uniqueOverlayTree(RedirectingFileSystem *FS, 0
1734 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *SrcE, ----
1735 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *NewParentE = nullptr) { ----
1736 StringRef Name = SrcE->getName(); 0
1737 switch (SrcE->getKind()) { 0
1738 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_Directory: { 0
1739 auto *DE = cast(SrcE); 0
1740 // Empty directories could be present in the YAML as a way to ----
1741 // describe a file for a current directory after some of its subdir ----
1742 // is parsed. This only leads to redundant walks, ignore it. ----
1743 if (!Name.empty()) 0
1744 NewParentE = lookupOrCreateEntry(FS, Name, NewParentE); 0
1745 for (std::unique_ptr &SubEntry : 0
1746 llvm::make_range(DE->contents_begin(), DE->contents_end())) 0
1747 uniqueOverlayTree(FS, SubEntry.get(), NewParentE); 0
1748 break; 0
1749 } ----
1750 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_DirectoryRemap: { 0
1751 assert(NewParentE && "Parent entry must exist"); 0
1752 auto *DR = cast(SrcE); 0
1753 auto *DE = cast(NewParentE); 0
1754 DE->addContent( 0
1755 std::make_unique( 0
1756 Name, DR->getExternalContentsPath(), DR->getUseName())); 0
1757 break; 0
1758 } ----
1759 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_File: { 0
1760 assert(NewParentE && "Parent entry must exist"); 0
1761 auto *FE = cast(SrcE); 0
1762 auto *DE = cast(NewParentE); 0
1763 DE->addContent(std::make_unique( 0
1764 Name, FE->getExternalContentsPath(), FE->getUseName())); 0
1765 break; 0
1766 } ----
1767 } ----
1768 } 0
1769 ----
1770 std::unique_ptr ----
1771 parseEntry(yaml::Node *N, RedirectingFileSystem *FS, bool IsRootEntry) { 0
1772 auto *M = dyn_cast(N); 0
1773 if (!M) { 0
1774 error(N, "expected mapping node for file or directory entry"); 0
1775 return nullptr; 0
1776 } ----
1777 ----
1778 KeyStatusPair Fields[] = { ----
1779 KeyStatusPair("name", true), ----
1780 KeyStatusPair("type", true), ----
1781 KeyStatusPair("contents", false), ----
1782 KeyStatusPair("external-contents", false), ----
1783 KeyStatusPair("use-external-name", false), ----
1784 }; 0
1785 ----
1786 DenseMap Keys(std::begin(Fields), std::end(Fields)); 0
1787 ----
1788 enum { CF_NotSet, CF_List, CF_External } ContentsField = CF_NotSet; 0
1789 std::vector> ----
1790 EntryArrayContents; 0
1791 SmallString<256> ExternalContentsPath; 0
1792 SmallString<256> Name; 0
1793 yaml::Node *NameValueNode = nullptr; 0
1794 auto UseExternalName = RedirectingFileSystem::NK_NotSet; 0
1795 RedirectingFileSystem::EntryKind Kind; ----
1796 ----
1797 for (auto &I : *M) { 0
1798 StringRef Key; 0
1799 // Reuse the buffer for key and value, since we don't look at key after ----
1800 // parsing value. ----
1801 SmallString<256> Buffer; 0
1802 if (!parseScalarString(I.getKey(), Key, Buffer)) 0
1803 return nullptr; 0
1804 ----
1805 if (!checkDuplicateOrUnknownKey(I.getKey(), Key, Keys)) 0
1806 return nullptr; 0
1807 ----
1808 StringRef Value; 0
1809 if (Key == "name") { 0
1810 if (!parseScalarString(I.getValue(), Value, Buffer)) 0
1811 return nullptr; 0
1812 ----
1813 NameValueNode = I.getValue(); 0
1814 // Guarantee that old YAML files containing paths with ".." and "." ----
1815 // are properly canonicalized before read into the VFS. ----
1816 Name = canonicalize(Value).str(); 0
1817 } else if (Key == "type") { 0
1818 if (!parseScalarString(I.getValue(), Value, Buffer)) 0
1819 return nullptr; 0
1820 if (Value == "file") 0
1821 Kind = RedirectingFileSystem::EK_File; 0
1822 else if (Value == "directory") 0
1823 Kind = RedirectingFileSystem::EK_Directory; 0
1824 else if (Value == "directory-remap") 0
1825 Kind = RedirectingFileSystem::EK_DirectoryRemap; 0
1826 else { ----
1827 error(I.getValue(), "unknown value for 'type'"); 0
1828 return nullptr; 0
1829 } ----
1830 } else if (Key == "contents") { 0
1831 if (ContentsField != CF_NotSet) { 0
1832 error(I.getKey(), 0
1833 "entry already has 'contents' or 'external-contents'"); ----
1834 return nullptr; 0
1835 } ----
1836 ContentsField = CF_List; 0
1837 auto *Contents = dyn_cast(I.getValue()); 0
1838 if (!Contents) { 0
1839 // FIXME: this is only for directories, what about files? ----
1840 error(I.getValue(), "expected array"); 0
1841 return nullptr; 0
1842 } ----
1843 ----
1844 for (auto &I : *Contents) { 0
1845 if (std::unique_ptr E = 0
1846 parseEntry(&I, FS, /*IsRootEntry*/ false)) 0
1847 EntryArrayContents.push_back(std::move(E)); 0
1848 else ----
1849 return nullptr; 0
1850 } ----
1851 } else if (Key == "external-contents") { 0
1852 if (ContentsField != CF_NotSet) { 0
1853 error(I.getKey(), 0
1854 "entry already has 'contents' or 'external-contents'"); ----
1855 return nullptr; 0
1856 } ----
1857 ContentsField = CF_External; 0
1858 if (!parseScalarString(I.getValue(), Value, Buffer)) 0
1859 return nullptr; 0
1860 ----
1861 SmallString<256> FullPath; 0
1862 if (FS->IsRelativeOverlay) { 0
1863 FullPath = FS->getOverlayFileDir(); 0
1864 assert(!FullPath.empty() && 0
1865 "External contents prefix directory must exist"); ----
1866 llvm::sys::path::append(FullPath, Value); 0
1867 } else { ----
1868 FullPath = Value; 0
1869 } ----
1870 ----
1871 // Guarantee that old YAML files containing paths with ".." and "." ----
1872 // are properly canonicalized before read into the VFS. ----
1873 FullPath = canonicalize(FullPath); 0
1874 ExternalContentsPath = FullPath.str(); 0
1875 } else if (Key == "use-external-name") { 0
1876 bool Val; ----
1877 if (!parseScalarBool(I.getValue(), Val)) 0
1878 return nullptr; 0
1879 UseExternalName = Val ? RedirectingFileSystem::NK_External 0
1880 : RedirectingFileSystem::NK_Virtual; ----
1881 } else { ----
1882 llvm_unreachable("key missing from Keys"); 0
1883 } ----
1884 } 0
1885 ----
1886 if (Stream.failed()) 0
1887 return nullptr; 0
1888 ----
1889 // check for missing keys ----
1890 if (ContentsField == CF_NotSet) { 0
1891 error(N, "missing key 'contents' or 'external-contents'"); 0
1892 return nullptr; 0
1893 } ----
1894 if (!checkMissingKeys(N, Keys)) 0
1895 return nullptr; 0
1896 ----
1897 // check invalid configuration ----
1898 if (Kind == RedirectingFileSystem::EK_Directory && 0
1899 UseExternalName != RedirectingFileSystem::NK_NotSet) { 0
1900 error(N, "'use-external-name' is not supported for 'directory' entries"); 0
1901 return nullptr; 0
1902 } ----
1903 ----
1904 if (Kind == RedirectingFileSystem::EK_DirectoryRemap && 0
1905 ContentsField == CF_List) { ----
1906 error(N, "'contents' is not supported for 'directory-remap' entries"); 0
1907 return nullptr; 0
1908 } ----
1909 ----
1910 sys::path::Style path_style = sys::path::Style::native; 0
1911 if (IsRootEntry) { 0
1912 // VFS root entries may be in either Posix or Windows style. Figure out ----
1913 // which style we have, and use it consistently. ----
1914 if (sys::path::is_absolute(Name, sys::path::Style::posix)) { 0
1915 path_style = sys::path::Style::posix; 0
1916 } else if (sys::path::is_absolute(Name, 0
1917 sys::path::Style::windows_backslash)) { ----
1918 path_style = sys::path::Style::windows_backslash; 0
1919 } else { ----
1920 // Relative VFS root entries are made absolute to either the overlay ----
1921 // directory, or the current working directory, then we can determine ----
1922 // the path style from that. ----
1923 std::error_code EC; 0
1924 if (FS->RootRelative == 0
1925 RedirectingFileSystem::RootRelativeKind::OverlayDir) { ----
1926 StringRef FullPath = FS->getOverlayFileDir(); 0
1927 assert(!FullPath.empty() && "Overlay file directory must exist"); 0
1928 EC = FS->makeAbsolute(FullPath, Name); 0
1929 Name = canonicalize(Name); 0
1930 } else { ----
1931 EC = sys::fs::make_absolute(Name); 0
1932 } ----
1933 if (EC) { 0
1934 assert(NameValueNode && "Name presence should be checked earlier"); 0
1935 error( 0
1936 NameValueNode, ----
1937 "entry with relative path at the root level is not discoverable"); ----
1938 return nullptr; 0
1939 } ----
1940 path_style = sys::path::is_absolute(Name, sys::path::Style::posix) 0
1941 ? sys::path::Style::posix 0
1942 : sys::path::Style::windows_backslash; ----
1943 } ----
1944 // is::path::is_absolute(Name, sys::path::Style::windows_backslash) will ----
1945 // return true even if `Name` is using forward slashes. Distinguish ----
1946 // between windows_backslash and windows_slash. ----
1947 if (path_style == sys::path::Style::windows_backslash && 0
1948 getExistingStyle(Name) != sys::path::Style::windows_backslash) 0
1949 path_style = sys::path::Style::windows_slash; 0
1950 } ----
1951 ----
1952 // Remove trailing slash(es), being careful not to remove the root path ----
1953 StringRef Trimmed = Name; 0
1954 size_t RootPathLen = sys::path::root_path(Trimmed, path_style).size(); 0
1955 while (Trimmed.size() > RootPathLen && 0
1956 sys::path::is_separator(Trimmed.back(), path_style)) 0
1957 Trimmed = Trimmed.slice(0, Trimmed.size() - 1); 0
1958 ----
1959 // Get the last component ----
1960 StringRef LastComponent = sys::path::filename(Trimmed, path_style); 0
1961 ----
1962 std::unique_ptr Result; 0
1963 switch (Kind) { 0
1964 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_File: 0
1965 Result = std::make_unique( 0
1966 LastComponent, std::move(ExternalContentsPath), UseExternalName); 0
1967 break; 0
1968 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_DirectoryRemap: 0
1969 Result = std::make_unique( 0
1970 LastComponent, std::move(ExternalContentsPath), UseExternalName); 0
1971 break; 0
1972 case RedirectingFileSystem::EK_Directory: 0
1973 Result = std::make_unique( 0
1974 LastComponent, std::move(EntryArrayContents), 0
1975 Status("", getNextVirtualUniqueID(), std::chrono::system_clock::now(), 0
1976 0, 0, 0, file_type::directory_file, sys::fs::all_all)); 0
1977 break; 0
1978 } ----
1979 ----
1980 StringRef Parent = sys::path::parent_path(Trimmed, path_style); 0
1981 if (Parent.empty()) 0
1982 return Result; 0
1983 ----
1984 // if 'name' contains multiple components, create implicit directory entries ----
1985 for (sys::path::reverse_iterator I = sys::path::rbegin(Parent, path_style), 0
1986 E = sys::path::rend(Parent); 0
1987 I != E; ++I) { 0
1988 std::vector> Entries; 0
1989 Entries.push_back(std::move(Result)); 0
1990 Result = std::make_unique( 0
1991 *I, std::move(Entries), 0
1992 Status("", getNextVirtualUniqueID(), std::chrono::system_clock::now(), 0
1993 0, 0, 0, file_type::directory_file, sys::fs::all_all)); 0
1994 } 0
1995 return Result; 0
1996 } 0
1997 ----
1998 public: ----
1999 RedirectingFileSystemParser(yaml::Stream &S) : Stream(S) {} 0
2000 ----
2001 // false on error ----
2002 bool parse(yaml::Node *Root, RedirectingFileSystem *FS) { 0
2003 auto *Top = dyn_cast(Root); 0
2004 if (!Top) { 0
2005 error(Root, "expected mapping node"); 0
2006 return false; 0
2007 } ----
2008 ----
2009 KeyStatusPair Fields[] = { ----
2010 KeyStatusPair("version", true), ----
2011 KeyStatusPair("case-sensitive", false), ----
2012 KeyStatusPair("use-external-names", false), ----
2013 KeyStatusPair("root-relative", false), ----
2014 KeyStatusPair("overlay-relative", false), ----
2015 KeyStatusPair("fallthrough", false), ----
2016 KeyStatusPair("redirecting-with", false), ----
2017 KeyStatusPair("roots", true), ----
2018 }; 0
2019 ----
2020 DenseMap Keys(std::begin(Fields), std::end(Fields)); 0
2021 std::vector> RootEntries; 0
2022 ----
2023 // Parse configuration and 'roots' ----
2024 for (auto &I : *Top) { 0
2025 SmallString<10> KeyBuffer; 0
2026 StringRef Key; 0
2027 if (!parseScalarString(I.getKey(), Key, KeyBuffer)) 0
2028 return false; 0
2029 ----
2030 if (!checkDuplicateOrUnknownKey(I.getKey(), Key, Keys)) 0
2031 return false; 0
2032 ----
2033 if (Key == "roots") { 0
2034 auto *Roots = dyn_cast(I.getValue()); 0
2035 if (!Roots) { 0
2036 error(I.getValue(), "expected array"); 0
2037 return false; 0
2038 } ----
2039 ----
2040 for (auto &I : *Roots) { 0
2041 if (std::unique_ptr E = 0
2042 parseEntry(&I, FS, /*IsRootEntry*/ true)) 0
2043 RootEntries.push_back(std::move(E)); 0
2044 else ----
2045 return false; 0
2046 } ----
2047 } else if (Key == "version") { 0
2048 StringRef VersionString; 0
2049 SmallString<4> Storage; 0
2050 if (!parseScalarString(I.getValue(), VersionString, Storage)) 0
2051 return false; 0
2052 int Version; ----
2053 if (VersionString.getAsInteger(10, Version)) { 0
2054 error(I.getValue(), "expected integer"); 0
2055 return false; 0
2056 } ----
2057 if (Version < 0) { 0
2058 error(I.getValue(), "invalid version number"); 0
2059 return false; 0
2060 } ----
2061 if (Version != 0) { 0
2062 error(I.getValue(), "version mismatch, expected 0"); 0
2063 return false; 0
2064 } ----
2065 } else if (Key == "case-sensitive") { 0
2066 if (!parseScalarBool(I.getValue(), FS->CaseSensitive)) 0
2067 return false; 0
2068 } else if (Key == "overlay-relative") { 0
2069 if (!parseScalarBool(I.getValue(), FS->IsRelativeOverlay)) 0
2070 return false; 0
2071 } else if (Key == "use-external-names") { 0
2072 if (!parseScalarBool(I.getValue(), FS->UseExternalNames)) 0
2073 return false; 0
2074 } else if (Key == "fallthrough") { 0
2075 if (Keys["redirecting-with"].Seen) { 0
2076 error(I.getValue(), 0
2077 "'fallthrough' and 'redirecting-with' are mutually exclusive"); ----
2078 return false; 0
2079 } ----
2080 ----
2081 bool ShouldFallthrough = false; 0
2082 if (!parseScalarBool(I.getValue(), ShouldFallthrough)) 0
2083 return false; 0
2084 ----
2085 if (ShouldFallthrough) { 0
2086 FS->Redirection = RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::Fallthrough; 0
2087 } else { ----
2088 FS->Redirection = RedirectingFileSystem::RedirectKind::RedirectOnly; 0
2089 } ----
2090 } else if (Key == "redirecting-with") { 0
2091 if (Keys["fallthrough"].Seen) { 0
2092 error(I.getValue(), 0
2093 "'fallthrough' and 'redirecting-with' are mutually exclusive"); ----
2094 return false; 0
2095 } ----
2096 ----
2097 if (auto Kind = parseRedirectKind(I.getValue())) { 0
2098 FS->Redirection = *Kind; 0
2099 } else { ----
2100 error(I.getValue(), "expected valid redirect kind"); 0
2101 return false; 0
2102 } ----
2103 } else if (Key == "root-relative") { 0
2104 if (auto Kind = parseRootRelativeKind(I.getValue())) { 0
2105 FS->RootRelative = *Kind; 0
2106 } else { ----
2107 error(I.getValue(), "expected valid root-relative kind"); 0
2108 return false; 0
2109 } ----
2110 } else { ----
2111 llvm_unreachable("key missing from Keys"); 0
2112 } ----
2113 } 0
2114 ----
2115 if (Stream.failed()) 0
2116 return false; 0
2117 ----
2118 if (!checkMissingKeys(Top, Keys)) 0
2119 return false; 0
2120 ----
2121 // Now that we sucessefully parsed the YAML file, canonicalize the internal ----
2122 // representation to a proper directory tree so that we can search faster ----
2123 // inside the VFS. ----
2124 for (auto &E : RootEntries) 0
2125 uniqueOverlayTree(FS, E.get()); 0
2126 ----
2127 return true; 0
2128 } 0
2129 }; ----
2130 ----
2131 std::unique_ptr ----
2132 RedirectingFileSystem::create(std::unique_ptr Buffer, 0
2133 SourceMgr::DiagHandlerTy DiagHandler, ----
2134 StringRef YAMLFilePath, void *DiagContext, ----
2135 IntrusiveRefCntPtr ExternalFS) { ----
2136 SourceMgr SM; 0
2137 yaml::Stream Stream(Buffer->getMemBufferRef(), SM); 0
2138 ----
2139 SM.setDiagHandler(DiagHandler, DiagContext); 0
2140 yaml::document_iterator DI = Stream.begin(); 0
2141 yaml::Node *Root = DI->getRoot(); 0
2142 if (DI == Stream.end() || !Root) { 0
2143 SM.PrintMessage(SMLoc(), SourceMgr::DK_Error, "expected root node"); 0
2144 return nullptr; 0
2145 } ----
2146 ----
2147 RedirectingFileSystemParser P(Stream); 0
2148 ----
2149 std::unique_ptr FS( ----
2150 new RedirectingFileSystem(ExternalFS)); 0
2151 ----
2152 if (!YAMLFilePath.empty()) { 0
2153 // Use the YAML path from -ivfsoverlay to compute the dir to be prefixed ----
2154 // to each 'external-contents' path. ----
2155 // ----
2156 // Example: ----
2157 // -ivfsoverlay dummy.cache/vfs/vfs.yaml ----
2158 // yields: ----
2159 // FS->OverlayFileDir => //dummy.cache/vfs ----
2160 // ----
2161 SmallString<256> OverlayAbsDir = sys::path::parent_path(YAMLFilePath); 0
2162 std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(OverlayAbsDir); 0
2163 assert(!EC && "Overlay dir final path must be absolute"); 0
2164 (void)EC; ----
2165 FS->setOverlayFileDir(OverlayAbsDir); 0
2166 } 0
2167 ----
2168 if (!P.parse(Root, FS.get())) 0
2169 return nullptr; 0
2170 ----
2171 return FS; 0
2172 } 0
2173 ----
2174 std::unique_ptr RedirectingFileSystem::create( 0
2175 ArrayRef> RemappedFiles, ----
2176 bool UseExternalNames, FileSystem &ExternalFS) { ----
2177 std::unique_ptr FS( ----
2178 new RedirectingFileSystem(&ExternalFS)); 0
2179 FS->UseExternalNames = UseExternalNames; 0
2180 ----
2181 StringMap Entries; 0
2182 ----
2183 for (auto &Mapping : llvm::reverse(RemappedFiles)) { 0
2184 SmallString<128> From = StringRef(Mapping.first); 0
2185 SmallString<128> To = StringRef(Mapping.second); 0
2186 { ----
2187 auto EC = ExternalFS.makeAbsolute(From); 0
2188 (void)EC; ----
2189 assert(!EC && "Could not make absolute path"); 0
2190 } ----
2191 ----
2192 // Check if we've already mapped this file. The first one we see (in the ----
2193 // reverse iteration) wins. ----
2194 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *&ToEntry = Entries[From]; 0
2195 if (ToEntry) 0
2196 continue; 0
2197 ----
2198 // Add parent directories. ----
2199 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *Parent = nullptr; 0
2200 StringRef FromDirectory = llvm::sys::path::parent_path(From); 0
2201 for (auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(FromDirectory), 0
2202 E = llvm::sys::path::end(FromDirectory); 0
2203 I != E; ++I) { 0
2204 Parent = RedirectingFileSystemParser::lookupOrCreateEntry(FS.get(), *I, 0
2205 Parent); ----
2206 } ----
2207 assert(Parent && "File without a directory?"); 0
2208 { ----
2209 auto EC = ExternalFS.makeAbsolute(To); 0
2210 (void)EC; ----
2211 assert(!EC && "Could not make absolute path"); 0
2212 } ----
2213 ----
2214 // Add the file. ----
2215 auto NewFile = std::make_unique( ----
2216 llvm::sys::path::filename(From), To, 0
2217 UseExternalNames ? RedirectingFileSystem::NK_External 0
2218 : RedirectingFileSystem::NK_Virtual); 0
2219 ToEntry = NewFile.get(); 0
2220 cast(Parent)->addContent( 0
2221 std::move(NewFile)); 0
2222 } 0
2223 ----
2224 return FS; 0
2225 } 0
2226 ----
2227 RedirectingFileSystem::LookupResult::LookupResult( 0
2228 Entry *E, sys::path::const_iterator Start, sys::path::const_iterator End) ----
2229 : E(E) { 0
2230 assert(E != nullptr); 0
2231 // If the matched entry is a DirectoryRemapEntry, set ExternalRedirect to the ----
2232 // path of the directory it maps to in the external file system plus any ----
2233 // remaining path components in the provided iterator. ----
2234 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast(E)) { 0
2235 SmallString<256> Redirect(DRE->getExternalContentsPath()); 0
2236 sys::path::append(Redirect, Start, End, 0
2237 getExistingStyle(DRE->getExternalContentsPath())); ----
2238 ExternalRedirect = std::string(Redirect); 0
2239 } 0
2240 } 0
2241 ----
2242 void RedirectingFileSystem::LookupResult::getPath( 0
2243 llvm::SmallVectorImpl &Result) const { ----
2244 Result.clear(); 0
2245 for (Entry *Parent : Parents) 0
2246 llvm::sys::path::append(Result, Parent->getName()); 0
2247 llvm::sys::path::append(Result, E->getName()); 0
2248 } 0

2250 std::error_code ----
2251 RedirectingFileSystem::makeCanonical(SmallVectorImpl &Path) const { 0
2252 if (std::error_code EC = makeAbsolute(Path)) 0
2253 return EC; 0
2254 ----
2255 llvm::SmallString<256> CanonicalPath = ----
2256 canonicalize(StringRef(Path.data(), Path.size())); 0
2257 if (CanonicalPath.empty()) 0
2258 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::invalid_argument); 0
2259 ----
2260 Path.assign(CanonicalPath.begin(), CanonicalPath.end()); 0
2261 return {}; 0
2262 } 0
2263 ----
2264 ErrorOr ----
2265 RedirectingFileSystem::lookupPath(StringRef Path) const { 0
2266 sys::path::const_iterator Start = sys::path::begin(Path); 0
2267 sys::path::const_iterator End = sys::path::end(Path); 0
2268 llvm::SmallVector Entries; 0
2269 for (const auto &Root : Roots) { 0
2270 ErrorOr Result = ----
2271 lookupPathImpl(Start, End, Root.get(), Entries); 0
2272 if (Result || Result.getError() != llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory) { 0
2273 Result->Parents = std::move(Entries); 0
2274 return Result; 0
2275 } ----
2276 } 0
2277 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory); 0
2278 } 0
2279 ----
2280 ErrorOr ----
2281 RedirectingFileSystem::lookupPathImpl( 0
2282 sys::path::const_iterator Start, sys::path::const_iterator End, ----
2283 RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *From, ----
2284 llvm::SmallVectorImpl &Entries) const { ----
2285 assert(!isTraversalComponent(*Start) && 0
2286 !isTraversalComponent(From->getName()) && ----
2287 "Paths should not contain traversal components"); ----
2288 ----
2289 StringRef FromName = From->getName(); 0
2290 ----
2291 // Forward the search to the next component in case this is an empty one. ----
2292 if (!FromName.empty()) { 0
2293 if (!pathComponentMatches(*Start, FromName)) 0
2294 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory); 0
2295 ----
2296 ++Start; 0
2297 ----
2298 if (Start == End) { 0
2299 // Match! ----
2300 return LookupResult(From, Start, End); 0
2301 } ----
2302 } ----
2303 ----
2304 if (isa(From)) 0
2305 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::not_a_directory); 0
2306 ----
2307 if (isa(From)) 0
2308 return LookupResult(From, Start, End); 0
2309 ----
2310 auto *DE = cast(From); 0
2311 for (const std::unique_ptr &DirEntry : 0
2312 llvm::make_range(DE->contents_begin(), DE->contents_end())) { 0
2313 Entries.push_back(From); 0
2314 ErrorOr Result = ----
2315 lookupPathImpl(Start, End, DirEntry.get(), Entries); 0
2316 if (Result || Result.getError() != llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory) 0
2317 return Result; 0
2318 Entries.pop_back(); 0
2319 } 0
2320 ----
2321 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::no_such_file_or_directory); 0
2322 } ----
2323 ----
2324 static Status getRedirectedFileStatus(const Twine &OriginalPath, 0
2325 bool UseExternalNames, ----
2326 Status ExternalStatus) { ----
2327 // The path has been mapped by some nested VFS and exposes an external path, ----
2328 // don't override it with the original path. ----
2329 if (ExternalStatus.ExposesExternalVFSPath) 0
2330 return ExternalStatus; 0
2331 ----
2332 Status S = ExternalStatus; 0
2333 if (!UseExternalNames) 0
2334 S = Status::copyWithNewName(S, OriginalPath); 0
2335 else ----
2336 S.ExposesExternalVFSPath = true; 0
2337 S.IsVFSMapped = true; 0
2338 return S; 0
2339 } 0
2340 ----
2341 ErrorOr RedirectingFileSystem::status( 0
2342 const Twine &CanonicalPath, const Twine &OriginalPath, ----
2343 const RedirectingFileSystem::LookupResult &Result) { ----
2344 if (std::optional ExtRedirect = Result.getExternalRedirect()) { 0
2345 SmallString<256> CanonicalRemappedPath((*ExtRedirect).str()); 0
2346 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(CanonicalRemappedPath)) 0
2347 return EC; 0
2348 ----
2349 ErrorOr S = ExternalFS->status(CanonicalRemappedPath); 0
2350 if (!S) 0
2351 return S; 0
2352 S = Status::copyWithNewName(*S, *ExtRedirect); 0
2353 auto *RE = cast(Result.E); 0
2354 return getRedirectedFileStatus(OriginalPath, 0
2355 RE->useExternalName(UseExternalNames), *S); 0
2356 } 0
2357 ----
2358 auto *DE = cast(Result.E); 0
2359 return Status::copyWithNewName(DE->getStatus(), CanonicalPath); 0
2360 } ----
2361 ----
2362 ErrorOr ----
2363 RedirectingFileSystem::getExternalStatus(const Twine &CanonicalPath, 0
2364 const Twine &OriginalPath) const { ----
2365 auto Result = ExternalFS->status(CanonicalPath); 0
2366 ----
2367 // The path has been mapped by some nested VFS, don't override it with the ----
2368 // original path. ----
2369 if (!Result || Result->ExposesExternalVFSPath) 0
2370 return Result; 0
2371 return Status::copyWithNewName(Result.get(), OriginalPath); 0
2372 } 0
2373 ----
2374 ErrorOr RedirectingFileSystem::status(const Twine &OriginalPath) { 0
2375 SmallString<256> CanonicalPath; 0
2376 OriginalPath.toVector(CanonicalPath); 0
2377 ----
2378 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(CanonicalPath)) 0
2379 return EC; 0
2380 ----
2381 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallback) { 0
2382 // Attempt to find the original file first, only falling back to the ----
2383 // mapped file if that fails. ----
2384 ErrorOr S = getExternalStatus(CanonicalPath, OriginalPath); 0
2385 if (S) 0
2386 return S; 0
2387 } 0
2388 ----
2389 ErrorOr Result = ----
2390 lookupPath(CanonicalPath); 0
2391 if (!Result) { 0
2392 // Was not able to map file, fallthrough to using the original path if ----
2393 // that was the specified redirection type. ----
2394 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2395 isFileNotFound(Result.getError())) 0
2396 return getExternalStatus(CanonicalPath, OriginalPath); 0
2397 return Result.getError(); 0
2398 } ----
2399 ----
2400 ErrorOr S = status(CanonicalPath, OriginalPath, *Result); 0
2401 if (!S && Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2402 isFileNotFound(S.getError(), Result->E)) { 0
2403 // Mapped the file but it wasn't found in the underlying filesystem, ----
2404 // fallthrough to using the original path if that was the specified ----
2405 // redirection type. ----
2406 return getExternalStatus(CanonicalPath, OriginalPath); 0
2407 } ----
2408 ----
2409 return S; 0
2410 } 0

2424 ErrorOr> ----

2429 IsVolatile); 0

2439 ErrorOr> ----
2440 File::getWithPath(ErrorOr> Result, const Twine &P) { 0
2441 // See \c getRedirectedFileStatus - don't update path if it's exposing an ----
2442 // external path. ----
2443 if (!Result || (*Result)->status()->ExposesExternalVFSPath) 0
2444 return Result; 0
2445 ----
2446 ErrorOr> F = std::move(*Result); 0
2447 auto Name = F->get()->getName(); 0
2448 if (Name && Name.get() != P.str()) 0
2449 F->get()->setPath(P); 0
2450 return F; 0
2451 } 0
2452 ----
2453 ErrorOr> ----
2454 RedirectingFileSystem::openFileForRead(const Twine &OriginalPath) { 0
2455 SmallString<256> CanonicalPath; 0
2456 OriginalPath.toVector(CanonicalPath); 0
2457 ----
2458 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(CanonicalPath)) 0
2459 return EC; 0
2460 ----
2461 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallback) { 0
2462 // Attempt to find the original file first, only falling back to the ----
2463 // mapped file if that fails. ----
2464 auto F = File::getWithPath(ExternalFS->openFileForRead(CanonicalPath), 0
2465 OriginalPath); 0
2466 if (F) 0
2467 return F; 0
2468 } 0
2469 ----
2470 ErrorOr Result = ----
2471 lookupPath(CanonicalPath); 0
2472 if (!Result) { 0
2473 // Was not able to map file, fallthrough to using the original path if ----
2474 // that was the specified redirection type. ----
2475 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2476 isFileNotFound(Result.getError())) 0
2477 return File::getWithPath(ExternalFS->openFileForRead(CanonicalPath), 0
2478 OriginalPath); 0
2479 return Result.getError(); 0
2480 } ----
2481 ----
2482 if (!Result->getExternalRedirect()) // FIXME: errc::not_a_file? 0
2483 return make_error_code(llvm::errc::invalid_argument); 0
2484 ----
2485 StringRef ExtRedirect = *Result->getExternalRedirect(); 0
2486 SmallString<256> CanonicalRemappedPath(ExtRedirect.str()); 0
2487 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(CanonicalRemappedPath)) 0
2488 return EC; 0
2489 ----
2490 auto *RE = cast(Result->E); 0
2491 ----
2492 auto ExternalFile = File::getWithPath( ----
2493 ExternalFS->openFileForRead(CanonicalRemappedPath), ExtRedirect); 0
2494 if (!ExternalFile) { 0
2495 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2496 isFileNotFound(ExternalFile.getError(), Result->E)) { 0
2497 // Mapped the file but it wasn't found in the underlying filesystem, ----
2498 // fallthrough to using the original path if that was the specified ----
2499 // redirection type. ----
2500 return File::getWithPath(ExternalFS->openFileForRead(CanonicalPath), 0
2501 OriginalPath); 0
2502 } ----
2503 return ExternalFile; 0
2504 } ----
2505 ----
2506 auto ExternalStatus = (*ExternalFile)->status(); 0
2507 if (!ExternalStatus) 0
2508 return ExternalStatus.getError(); 0
2509 ----
2510 // Otherwise, the file was successfully remapped. Mark it as such. Also ----
2511 // replace the underlying path if the external name is being used. ----
2512 Status S = getRedirectedFileStatus( ----
2513 OriginalPath, RE->useExternalName(UseExternalNames), *ExternalStatus); 0
2514 return std::unique_ptr( 0
2515 std::make_unique(std::move(*ExternalFile), S)); 0
2516 } 0
2517 ----
2518 std::error_code ----
2519 RedirectingFileSystem::getRealPath(const Twine &OriginalPath, 0
2520 SmallVectorImpl &Output) const { ----
2521 SmallString<256> CanonicalPath; 0
2522 OriginalPath.toVector(CanonicalPath); 0
2523 ----
2524 if (std::error_code EC = makeCanonical(CanonicalPath)) 0
2525 return EC; 0
2526 ----
2527 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallback) { 0
2528 // Attempt to find the original file first, only falling back to the ----
2529 // mapped file if that fails. ----
2530 std::error_code EC = ExternalFS->getRealPath(CanonicalPath, Output); 0
2531 if (!EC) 0
2532 return EC; 0
2533 } ----
2534 ----
2535 ErrorOr Result = ----
2536 lookupPath(CanonicalPath); 0
2537 if (!Result) { 0
2538 // Was not able to map file, fallthrough to using the original path if ----
2539 // that was the specified redirection type. ----
2540 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2541 isFileNotFound(Result.getError())) 0
2542 return ExternalFS->getRealPath(CanonicalPath, Output); 0
2543 return Result.getError(); 0
2544 } ----
2545 ----
2546 // If we found FileEntry or DirectoryRemapEntry, look up the mapped ----
2547 // path in the external file system. ----
2548 if (auto ExtRedirect = Result->getExternalRedirect()) { 0
2549 auto P = ExternalFS->getRealPath(*ExtRedirect, Output); 0
2550 if (P && Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough && 0
2551 isFileNotFound(P, Result->E)) { 0
2552 // Mapped the file but it wasn't found in the underlying filesystem, ----
2553 // fallthrough to using the original path if that was the specified ----
2554 // redirection type. ----
2555 return ExternalFS->getRealPath(CanonicalPath, Output); 0
2556 } ----
2557 return P; 0
2558 } ----
2559 ----
2560 // We found a DirectoryEntry, which does not have a single external contents ----
2561 // path. Use the canonical virtual path. ----
2562 if (Redirection == RedirectKind::Fallthrough) { 0

2579 static void getVFSEntries(RedirectingFileSystem::Entry *SrcE, 0
2580 SmallVectorImpl &Path, ----
2581 SmallVectorImpl &Entries) { ----

2599 for (auto &Comp : Path) 0
2600 llvm::sys::path::append(VPath, Comp); 0

2602 YAMLVFSEntry(VPath.c_str(), DR->getExternalContentsPath())); 0

2605 ----
2606 assert(Kind == RedirectingFileSystem::EK_File && "Must be a EK_File"); 0
2607 auto *FE = dyn_cast(SrcE); 0

2609 SmallString<128> VPath; 0
2610 for (auto &Comp : Path) 0
2611 llvm::sys::path::append(VPath, Comp); 0
2612 Entries.push_back(YAMLVFSEntry(VPath.c_str(), FE->getExternalContentsPath())); 0

2684 ----
2685 bool JSONWriter::containedIn(StringRef Parent, StringRef Path) { 0
2686 using namespace llvm::sys; ----
2687 ----
2688 // Compare each path component. ----
2689 auto IParent = path::begin(Parent), EParent = path::end(Parent); 0
2690 for (auto IChild = path::begin(Path), EChild = path::end(Path); 0
2691 IParent != EParent && IChild != EChild; ++IParent, ++IChild) { 0
2692 if (*IParent != *IChild) 0
2693 return false; 0
2694 } ----
2695 // Have we exhausted the parent path? ----
2696 return IParent == EParent; 0
2697 } ----
2698 ----
2699 StringRef JSONWriter::containedPart(StringRef Parent, StringRef Path) { 0
2700 assert(!Parent.empty()); 0
2701 assert(containedIn(Parent, Path)); 0
2702 return Path.slice(Parent.size() + 1, StringRef::npos); 0
2703 } ----

2711 OS.indent(Indent + 2) << "'type': 'directory',\n"; 0
2712 OS.indent(Indent + 2) << "'name': \"" << llvm::yaml::escape(Name) << "\",\n"; 0
2713 OS.indent(Indent + 2) << "'contents': [\n"; 0
2714 } 0
2715 ----
2716 void JSONWriter::endDirectory() { 0
2717 unsigned Indent = getDirIndent(); 0
2718 OS.indent(Indent + 2) << "]\n"; 0
2719 OS.indent(Indent) << "}"; 0
2720 ----
2721 DirStack.pop_back(); 0
2722 } 0

2729 OS.indent(Indent + 2) << "'external-contents': \"" 0
2730 << llvm::yaml::escape(RPath) << "\"\n"; 0
2731 OS.indent(Indent) << "}"; 0
2732 } 0

2841 vfs::recursive_directory_iterator & ----
2842 recursive_directory_iterator::increment(std::error_code &EC) { 0
2843 assert(FS && State && !State->Stack.empty() && "incrementing past end"); 0
2844 assert(!State->Stack.top()->path().empty() && "non-canonical end iterator"); 0
2845 vfs::directory_iterator End; 0
2846 ----
2847 if (State->HasNoPushRequest) 0
2848 State->HasNoPushRequest = false; 0
2849 else { ----
2850 if (State->Stack.top()->type() == sys::fs::file_type::directory_file) { 0
2851 vfs::directory_iterator I = FS->dir_begin(State->Stack.top()->path(), EC); 0
2852 if (I != End) { 0
2853 State->Stack.push(I); 0
2854 return *this; 0
2855 } ----
2856 } 0
2857 } ----
2858 ----
2859 while (!State->Stack.empty() && State->Stack.top().increment(EC) == End) 0
2860 State->Stack.pop(); 0
2861 ----
2862 if (State->Stack.empty()) 0
2863 State.reset(); // end iterator 0
2864 ----
2865 return *this; 0
2866 } 0
